OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Ruth Bourne
OL,5,FMrs Bourne remembers only a handful of
OL,6,FBombes when she arrived. Eventually
OL,7,Fthere were more than 200.
OL,9,FThe work was so intensive that at
OL,10,Ffirst she didn't appreciate how much
OL,11,Fthe Bletchley codebreakers had helped
OL,12,Fwith the planning of D-Day.
OL,14,F"I didn't really comprehend the
OL,15,Fenormity of what was going on. I
OL,16,Fbelieve now that the information that
OL,17,Fwas given from Bletchley was
OL,18,Finvaluable.
